<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Repair on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/repair/</link><description>Recent content in Repair on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/repair/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] DLL Is Corrupt or Missing — Fix Corrupted DLL Files</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/dll-corrupt/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/dll-corrupt/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="dll-is-corrupt-or-missing"&gt;DLL Is Corrupt or Missing&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A corrupt DLL file produces errors ranging from &amp;ldquo;file is corrupt&amp;rdquo; messages to application crashes and blue screens. Windows may report:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Windows cannot verify the digital signature for this file.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The file [filename].dll is corrupt.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DLL files can become corrupted due to disk errors, interrupted writes, malware, or failed Windows updates. A corrupted DLL may have valid file size but contain garbage data, causing the loader to reject it or the program to crash when it tries to use the corrupted functions.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] macOS Disk Utility Error — Couldn't Unmount / Verify / Repair Disk</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/disk-utility-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/disk-utility-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="disk-utility-error--couldnt-unmount--verify--repair-disk"&gt;Disk Utility Error — Couldn&amp;rsquo;t Unmount / Verify / Repair Disk&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Disk Utility errors occur when macOS cannot unmount, verify, or repair a disk or volume. These errors typically prevent you from running First Aid, erasing a disk, or modifying partitions. The most common variants are &amp;ldquo;Couldn&amp;rsquo;t unmount disk,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Verify failed,&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Operation not permitted.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Disk Utility relies on the &lt;code&gt;diskutil&lt;/code&gt; command-line tool under the hood. Errors occur when:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] macOS Recovery Mode Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-macos-recovery/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-macos-recovery/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="macos-recovery-mode-error-fix"&gt;macOS Recovery Mode Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recovery mode errors include Recovery not booting, &amp;ldquo;No users available&amp;rdquo; message, macOS Utilities not loading, or Internet Recovery failing to connect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;macOS Recovery is a dedicated partition (or Internet Recovery) that provides tools to repair disks, reinstall macOS, and restore from backups. When Recovery fails, you lose access to essential repair tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corrupt Recovery partition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internet Recovery unable to connect to Apple servers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disk corruption preventing Recovery boot&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Firmware password blocking Recovery access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;T2/Secure Enclave issues on newer Macs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-try-internet-recovery"&gt;1. Try Internet Recovery&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Intel: Hold Option+Cmd+R during startup&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Apple Silicon: Hold power button → Options → Continue&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Internet Recovery downloads Recovery from Apple&amp;#39;s servers&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-check-recovery-partition"&gt;2. Check Recovery partition&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# From a working macOS installation, check Recovery&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;diskutil list | grep -i recovery
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Verify Recovery disk integrity&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;diskutil verifyVolume /Volumes/Recovery
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-create-a-bootable-usb-installer"&gt;3. Create a bootable USB installer&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# On another Mac, create a bootable installer&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo /Applications/Install&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\ &lt;/span&gt;macOS&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\ &lt;/span&gt;Sonoma.app/Contents/Resources/createinstallmedia &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; --volume /Volumes/MyUSB
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Boot from USB: Hold Option during startup, select the USB drive&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-remove-firmware-password-if-blocking"&gt;4. Remove firmware password (if blocking)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Boot into Recovery&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Open Firmware Password Utility from Utilities menu&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Turn off the firmware password&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Restart and try Recovery again&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-boot-error"&gt;Boot Error&lt;/a&gt; — Mac won&amp;rsquo;t boot normally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-firmware-error"&gt;Firmware Error&lt;/a&gt; — firmware corruption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-efi-error"&gt;EFI Error&lt;/a&gt; — EFI boot issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Registry is Corrupted Error - How to Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/reg-corrupted/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/reg-corrupted/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="registry-is-corrupted-error"&gt;Registry is Corrupted Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when registry hive files are damaged or inconsistent. Symptoms include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applications failing to launch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Blue screen errors referencing &lt;code&gt;0xC000021A&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Windows failing to boot&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;System instability and random crashes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Registry hives are stored as binary files in &lt;code&gt;%SystemRoot%\System32\config\&lt;/code&gt;. Corruption can cause cascading system failures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Power loss during registry write&lt;/strong&gt; — abrupt shutdown corrupted the hive file.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disk errors&lt;/strong&gt; — bad sectors damaged the registry files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Malware&lt;/strong&gt; — malicious software corrupted or replaced registry entries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Failed Windows update&lt;/strong&gt; — interrupted update damaged registry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registry cleaner tools&lt;/strong&gt; — aggressive cleaning removed critical entries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="run-system-file-checker"&gt;Run System File Checker&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cmd" data-lang="cmd"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sfc /scannow
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="run-dism-to-repair-system-image"&gt;Run DISM to Repair System Image&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cmd" data-lang="cmd"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /RestoreHealth
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sfc /scannow
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-disk-for-errors"&gt;Check Disk for Errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cmd" data-lang="cmd"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;chkdsk C: /f /r
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Restart required if checking the system drive.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>SQLite Database Corrupted</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/sqlite/sqlite-corruption-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/sqlite/sqlite-corruption-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sqlite-database-corrupted"&gt;SQLite Database Corrupted&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A SQLite database corruption error occurs when the database file becomes unreadable due to disk errors, improper shutdown, or file system issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improper shutdown during write operation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disk errors or bad sectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;File system corruption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hardware failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-integrity"&gt;Check Integrity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sqlite3 mydb.sqlite &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;PRAGMA integrity_check;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="recover-data"&gt;Recover Data&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Export data to SQL&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sqlite3 mydb.sqlite .dump &amp;gt; recovered.sql
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Create new database&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sqlite3 newdb.sqlite &amp;lt; recovered.sql
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-backup-command"&gt;Use Backup Command&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sqlite3 mydb.sqlite &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;.backup backup.db&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-for-disk-errors"&gt;Check for Disk Errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;chkdsk C: /f /r &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Windows&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;fsck /dev/sda1 &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Linux&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-wal-mode-for-safety"&gt;Use WAL Mode for Safety&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;PRAGMA journal_mode&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;WAL;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sqlite3 mydb.sqlite &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;SELECT * FROM users;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Error: database disk image is malformed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Recover:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sqlite3 mydb.sqlite .dump &amp;gt; recovered.sql
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sqlite3 newdb.sqlite &amp;lt; recovered.sql
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/sqlite/io-error2/"&gt;I/O Error&lt;/a&gt; — I/O error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/sqlite/memory-error4/"&gt;Memory Error&lt;/a&gt; — out of memory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Windows Update Corrupted Files Error - How to Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/win32-windows-update-corrupt/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/win32-windows-update-corrupt/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="windows-update-corrupted-files-error"&gt;Windows Update Corrupted Files Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when Windows Update detects corrupted system files or update components. The error may read:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;We couldn&amp;rsquo;t install some updates because there was a problem.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Error encountered while installing updates.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Corrupted files can prevent updates from installing correctly and cause system instability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interrupted update&lt;/strong&gt; — Previous update was interrupted during installation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disk errors&lt;/strong&gt; — Storage corruption damaged system files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Malware damage&lt;/strong&gt; — Malicious software corrupted system components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Power loss&lt;/strong&gt; — System shutdown during update process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registry corruption&lt;/strong&gt; — Update-related registry entries are damaged.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="run-system-file-checker"&gt;Run System File Checker&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cmd" data-lang="cmd"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sfc /scannow
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="run-dism-to-repair-system-image"&gt;Run DISM to Repair System Image&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cmd" data-lang="cmd"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /CheckHealth
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /ScanHealth
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /RestoreHealth
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-dism-with-source"&gt;Use DISM with Source&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cmd" data-lang="cmd"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /RestoreHealth /Source:D:\Sources\install.wim
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="repair-windows-from-installation-media"&gt;Repair Windows from Installation Media&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Boot from Windows installation media.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;strong&gt;Repair your computer&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Choose &lt;strong&gt;Startup Repair&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If that fails, open &lt;strong&gt;Command Prompt&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cmd" data-lang="cmd"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sfc /scannow /offbootdir=C:\ /offwindir=C:\Windows
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-disk-for-errors"&gt;Check Disk for Errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cmd" data-lang="cmd"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;chkdsk C: /f /r
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="reset-windows-update-components"&gt;Reset Windows Update Components&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Stop-Service wuauserv -Force
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Stop-Service bits -Force
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Stop-Service cryptsvc -Force
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Stop-Service appidsvc -Force
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Stop-Service msiserver -Force
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Clear update cache&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remove-Item &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;C:\Windows\SoftwareDistribution\Download\*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remove-Item &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;C:\Windows\SoftwareDistribution\DataStore\*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remove-Item &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;C:\Windows\System32\catroot2\*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Start-Service msiserver
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Start-Service appidsvc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Start-Service cryptsvc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Start-Service bits
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Start-Service wuauserv
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-windows-event-logs"&gt;Check Windows Event Logs&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-WinEvent -LogName &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Microsoft-Windows-WindowsUpdateClient/Operational&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -MaxEvents &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;20&lt;/span&gt; | Where-Object { $_.LevelDisplayName &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-eq&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; } | Format-List TimeCreated, Message
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-system-restore"&gt;Use System Restore&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Get-ComputerRestorePoint
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Restore-Computer -RestorePoint &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Before Update&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/win32-windows-update-error/"&gt;Windows Update Error 0x80070002&lt;/a&gt; — Update files missing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/win32-windows-update-timeout/"&gt;Windows Update Timeout&lt;/a&gt; — Update timed out&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/reg-corrupted/"&gt;Registry Corrupted&lt;/a&gt; — Registry corruption&lt;/li&gt;
